# Module & Barrel Rules

Full standard: [docs/agent/standards/common/modules.md](../../docs/agent/standards/common/modules.md)
Skill: `.cursor/skills/module-design-pattern/SKILL.md`

- Every domain module has an `index.ts` barrel that exports only its public surface.
- Import from barrels only — never `import { Foo } from '../jobs/JobsService'` from outside the module.
- Domain modules import `src/core/` globals only. Cross-domain imports are **forbidden**.
- Only `src/core/` modules use `@Global()`. Domain modules never use `@Global()`.
- `@Module({ imports, providers, exports, controllers })` — nothing else in the decorator.
- One `NestJS module` per bounded context; one controller per resource.
- DI tokens for adapter interfaces: `export const JOB_SEARCH_SERVICE = Symbol('JOB_SEARCH_SERVICE')`.
